===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} - two wings facing opposite directions. Originally, it represented wings; then, according to Xu Shen, its meaning changed into "leave; disobey" ([[違]]). Eventually, it was used perhaps as a phonetic loan to mean "not to be".

Unrelated to the Kangxi radical [[韭]].

===Etymology===
{{och-l|非|tr=*pɯj}} is the fusion of the negation particle {{och-l|不|not}} and the copula {{och-l|惟|to be}}, attested in [[oracle bone script|oracle bone inscriptions]].

